{quote}Now lets take a closer look at snappy_boot in snappy-system.txt, the command that contains all the magic{quote}

Here it is. Nothing especial in porting Snappy to different SoC's.. Just need to find out current system bootload arguments and change them with Snappy's one

https://ograblog.wordpress.com/2015/01/25/porting-ubuntu-snappy-to-a-yet-unsupported-armhf-board/
